<HEADLINE>
FT  23 DEC 92 / Observer: Tail spin
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The spirit of amukadari - the 'descent from heaven' of Japanese civil
servants to senior positions in industry - appears to have been turned on
its head at Mazda. Kenichi Yamamoto, who developed the carmaker's rotary
engine and led its 1980s expansion, has stepped down as chairman, where he
is replaced by Norimasa Furuta, to become 'supreme adviser'.
</TEXT>
<PUB>The Financial Times
</PUB>
